<li id="cite_note-63"><b><a href="#cite_ref-63" title="">^</a></b> Hynes, 47–48, 148–163</li>
<li id="cite_note-64"><b><a href="#cite_ref-64" title="">^</a></b> Lytle, 217</li>
<li id="cite_note-65"><b><a href="#cite_ref-65" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFBaum2007">Baum, Rudy M. (June 4, 2007). "<a href="http://pubs.acs.org/isubscribe/journals/cen/85/i23/html/8523editor.html" class="external text" title="http://pubs.acs.org/isubscribe/journals/cen/85/i23/html/8523editor.html" rel="nofollow">Rachel Carson</a>". <i>Chemical and Engineering News</i> (American Chemical Society) <b>85</b> (23): 5<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://pubs.acs.org/isubscribe/journals/cen/85/i23/html/8523editor.html" class="external free" title="http://pubs.acs.org/isubscribe/journals/cen/85/i23/html/8523editor.html" rel="nofollow">http://pubs.acs.org/isubscribe/journals/cen/85/i23/html/8523editor.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Rachel+Carson&amp;rft.jtitle=Chemical+and+Engineering+News&amp;rft.aulast=Baum&amp;rft.aufirst=Rudy+M.&amp;rft.au=Baum%2C+Rudy+M.&amp;rft.date=June+4%2C+2007&amp;rft.volume=85&amp;rft.issue=23&amp;rft.pages=5&amp;rft.pub=American+Chemical+Society&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fpubs.acs.org%2Fisubscribe%2Fjournals%2Fcen%2F85%2Fi23%2Fhtml%2F8523editor.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Rachel_Carson"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Conservative_criticism_of_Carson-66"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Conservative_criticism_of_Carson_66-0" title="">^</a></b> Examples of recent criticism include:<br />
(a) Rich Karlgaard, "<a href="http://blogs.forbes.com/digitalrules/2007/05/but_her_heart_w.html" class="external text" title="http://blogs.forbes.com/digitalrules/2007/05/but_her_heart_w.html" rel="nofollow">But Her Heart Was Good</a>", Forbes.com, May 18, 2007. Accessed September 23, 2007.<br />
(b) Keith Lockitch, "<a href="http://capmag.com/article.asp?ID=4965" class="external text" title="http://capmag.com/article.asp?ID=4965" rel="nofollow">Rachel Carson's Genocide</a>", <i>Capitalism Magazine</i>, May 23, 2007. Accessed May 24, 2007<br />
(c) <a href="/wiki/David_Roberts_(journalist)" title="David Roberts (journalist)">David Roberts</a>, "<a href="http://gristmill.grist.org/story/2007/5/23/17433/0674" class="external text" title="http://gristmill.grist.org/story/2007/5/23/17433/0674" rel="nofollow">My one and only post on the Rachel Carson nonsense</a>" Grist.com, May 24, 2007. Accessed September 23, 2007.<br />
(d) Paul Driessen, "<a href="http://www.washingtontimes.com/commentary/20070428-100957-5274r.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.washingtontimes.com/commentary/20070428-100957-5274r.htm" rel="nofollow">Forty Years of Perverse 'Responsibility,'</a>", <i>The Washington Times</i>, April 29, 2007. Accessed May 30, 2007.<br />
(e) Iain Murray, "<a href="http://article.nationalreview.com/?q=MjhkYTlmYjljMmJlMzU5Y2IxOGM3ZWM3YzZkNzFiNGE" class="external text" title="http://article.nationalreview.com/?q=MjhkYTlmYjljMmJlMzU5Y2IxOGM3ZWM3YzZkNzFiNGE" rel="nofollow"><i>Silent</i> Alarmism: A Centennial We Could Do Without</a>", <i>National Review</i>, May 31, 2007. Accessed May 31, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-most_harmful-67"><b><a href="#cite_ref-most_harmful_67-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.humanevents.com/article.php?id=7591" class="external text" title="http://www.humanevents.com/article.php?id=7591" rel="nofollow">Ten Most Harmful Books of the 19th and 20th Centuries</a>. Retrieved August 24, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-68"><b><a href="#cite_ref-68" title="">^</a></b> Lytle, 217–220; Jeffrey K. Stine, "Natural Resources and Environmental Policy" in <i>The Reagan Presidency: Pragmatic Conservatism and Its Legacies</i>, edited by W. Elliott Browlee and Hugh Davis Graham. Lawrence, KS: University of Kansas Press, 2003. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0700612688" class="internal">ISBN 0-7006-1268-8</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-69"><b><a href="#cite_ref-69" title="">^</a></b> Lytle, 220–228</li>
<li id="cite_note-70"><b><a href="#cite_ref-70" title="">^</a></b> She instead argued in <i>Silent Spring</i> that:
<blockquote>
<p>No responsible person contends that insect-borne disease should be ignored. The question that has now urgently presented itself is whether it is either wise or responsible to attack the problem by methods that are rapidly making it worse. The world has heard much of the triumphant war against disease through the control of insect vectors of infection, but it has heard little of the other side of the story—the defeats, the short-lived triumphs that now strongly support the alarming view that the insect enemy has been made actually stronger by our efforts. Even worse, we may have destroyed our very means of fighting. (p. 266)</p>
</blockquote>
She noted that "Malaria programmes are threatened by resistance among mosquitoes" (p. 267) and emphasized the advice given by the director of Holland's Plant Protection Service: "Practical advice should be 'Spray as little as you possibly can' rather than 'Spray to the limit of your capacity'…Pressure on the pest population should always be as slight as possible." (p. 275)</li>
<li id="cite_note-71"><b><a href="#cite_ref-71" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.malaria.org/DDTpage.html" class="external text" title="http://www.malaria.org/DDTpage.html" rel="nofollow">Malaria Foundation International</a>. Retrieved March 15, 2006.</li>
<li id="cite_note-72"><b><a href="#cite_ref-72" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.pbs.org/moyers/journal/09212007/profile2.html" class="external text" title="http://www.pbs.org/moyers/journal/09212007/profile2.html" rel="nofollow">Rachel Carson and DDT</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Bill_Moyers_Journal" title="Bill Moyers Journal">Bill Moyers Journal</a></i>, September 21, 2007. Retrieved September 29, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-73"><b><a href="#cite_ref-73" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.medaloffreedom.com/RachelCarson.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.medaloffreedom.com/RachelCarson.htm" rel="nofollow">Presidential Medal of Freedom Recipient Rachel Carson</a>. Retrieved August 24, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-74"><b><a href="#cite_ref-74" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.rachelcarsonhomestead.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.rachelcarsonhomestead.org/" rel="nofollow">Rachel Carson Homestead</a>. Retrieved September 7, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-75"><b><a href="#cite_ref-75" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.marylandhistoricaltrust.net/nr/NRDetail.aspx?HDID=1094&amp;FROM=NRNHLList.aspx" class="external text" title="http://www.marylandhistoricaltrust.net/nr/NRDetail.aspx?HDID=1094&amp;FROM=NRNHLList.aspx" rel="nofollow">"Maryland Historical Trust"</a>. <i>National Register of Historic Places:</i> Properties in Montgomery County<i>. Maryland Historical Trust. 2008-06-08<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.marylandhistoricaltrust.net/nr/NRDetail.aspx?HDID=1094&amp;FROM=NRNHLList.aspx" class="external free" title="http://www.marylandhistoricaltrust.net/nr/NRDetail.aspx?HDID=1094&amp;FROM=NRNHLList.aspx" rel="nofollow">http://www.marylandhistoricaltrust.net/nr/NRDetail.aspx?HDID=1094&amp;FROM=NRNHLList.aspx</a></span>.</i></cite><i><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Maryland+Historical+Trust&amp;rft.atitle=National+Register+of+Historic+Places%3A%0AProperties+in+Montgomery+County&amp;rft.date=2008-06-08&amp;rft.pub=Maryland+Historical+Trust&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.marylandhistoricaltrust.net%2Fnr%2FNRDetail.aspx%3FHDID%3D1094%26FROM%3DNRNHLList.aspx&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Rachel_Carson"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></i></li>
<li id="cite_note-76"><b><a href="#cite_ref-76" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.rachelcarsontrails.org/rct" class="external text" title="http://www.rachelcarsontrails.org/rct" rel="nofollow">Rachel Carson Trail</a>. Retrieved September 26, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-bridge-77"><b><a href="#cite_ref-bridge_77-0" title="">^</a></b> Jerome L. Sherman, <a href="http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/06113/684423-85.stm" class="external text" title="http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/06113/684423-85.stm" rel="nofollow">"Environmentalist Rachel Carson's legacy remembered on Earth Day"</a>, <i>Pittsburgh Post-Gazette</i>, April 23, 2006. Retrieved September 23, 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-78"><b><a href="#cite_ref-78" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.montgomeryschoolsmd.org/schools/rachelcarsones/index.shtm" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.montgomeryschoolsmd.org/schools/rachelcarsones/index.shtm" rel="nofollow">[1]</a>. Retrieved February 22, 2008.</li>
